1→// Package strategy provides an interface for different git strategies
     2→// that can be used to save and manage Claude Code session changes.
     3→package strategy
     4→
     5→import (
     6→	"encoding/json"
     7→	"errors"
     8→	"os"
     9→	"strings"
    10→	"time"
    11→
    12→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent"
    13→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id"
    14→)
    15→
    16→// ErrNoMetadata is returned when a commit does not have an Entire metadata trailer.
    17→var ErrNoMetadata = errors.New("commit has no entire metadata")
    18→
    19→// ErrNoSession is returned when no session info is available.
    20→var ErrNoSession = errors.New("no session info available")
    21→
    22→// ErrNotTaskCheckpoint is returned when a rewind point is not a task checkpoint.
    23→var ErrNotTaskCheckpoint = errors.New("not a task checkpoint")
    24→
    25→// ErrNotImplemented is returned when a feature is not yet implemented.
    26→var ErrNotImplemented = errors.New("not implemented")
    27→
    28→// SessionIDConflictError is returned when trying to start a new session
    29→// but the shadow branch already has commits from a different session ID.
    30→// This prevents orphaning existing session work.
    31→type SessionIDConflictError struct {
    32→	ExistingSession string // Session ID found in the shadow branch
    33→	NewSession      string // Session ID being initialized
    34→	ShadowBranch    string // The shadow branch name (e.g., "entire/abc1234")
    35→}
    36→
    37→func (e *SessionIDConflictError) Error() string {
    38→	return "session ID conflict: shadow branch has commits from a different session"
    39→}
    40→
    41→// ExtractToolUseIDFromTaskMetadataDir extracts the ToolUseID from a task metadata directory path.
    42→// Task metadata dirs have format: .entire/metadata/<session>/tasks/<toolUseID>
    43→// Returns empty string if not a task metadata directory.
    44→func ExtractToolUseIDFromTaskMetadataDir(metadataDir string) string {
    45→	parts := strings.Split(metadataDir, "/")
    46→	if len(parts) >= 2 && parts[len(parts)-2] == "tasks" {
    47→		return parts[len(parts)-1]
    48→	}
    49→	return ""
    50→}
    51→
    52→// SessionInfo contains information about the current session state.
    53→// This is used to generate trailers for linking commits to their AI session.
    54→type SessionInfo struct {
    55→	// SessionID is the session identifier extracted from the latest commit's metadata
    56→	SessionID string
    57→
    58→	// Reference is a strategy-specific reference string.
    59→	// For manual-commit strategy: "entire/abc1234" (the shadow branch name)
    60→	// Empty for commit strategy (metadata is in the same commit).
    61→	Reference string
    62→
    63→	// CommitHash is the full SHA of the commit containing the session metadata.
    64→	// Empty for commit strategy.
    65→	CommitHash string
    66→}
    67→
    68→// RewindPoint represents a point to which the user can rewind.
    69→// This abstraction allows different strategies to use different
    70→// identifiers (commit hashes, branch names, stash refs, etc.)
    71→type RewindPoint struct {
    72→	// ID is the unique identifier for this rewind point
    73→	// (commit hash, branch name, stash ref, etc.)
    74→	ID string
    75→
    76→	// Message is the human-readable description/summary
    77→	Message string
    78→
    79→	// MetadataDir is the path to the metadata directory
    80→	MetadataDir string
    81→
    82→	// Date is when this rewind point was created
    83→	Date time.Time
    84→
    85→	// IsTaskCheckpoint indicates if this is a task checkpoint (vs a session checkpoint)
    86→	IsTaskCheckpoint bool
    87→
    88→	// ToolUseID is the tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session checkpoints)
    89→	ToolUseID string
    90→
    91→	// IsLogsOnly indicates this is a commit with session logs but no shadow branch state.
    92→	// The logs can be restored from entire/sessions, but file state requires git checkout.
    93→	IsLogsOnly bool
    94→
    95→	// CheckpointID is the stable 12-hex-char identifier for logs-only points.
    96→	// Used to retrieve logs from entire/sessions/<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/full.jsonl
    97→	// Empty for shadow branch checkpoints (uncommitted).
    98→	CheckpointID id.CheckpointID
    99→
   100→	// Agent is the human-readable name of the agent that created this checkpoint
   101→	// (e.g., "Claude Code", "Cursor")
   102→	Agent agent.AgentType
   103→
   104→	// SessionID is the session identifier for this checkpoint.
   105→	// Used to distinguish checkpoints from different concurrent sessions.
   106→	SessionID string
   107→
   108→	// SessionPrompt is the initial prompt that started this session.
   109→	// Used to help users identify which session a checkpoint belongs to.
   110→	SessionPrompt string
   111→
   112→	// SessionCount is the number of sessions in this checkpoint (1 for single-session).
   113→	// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.
   114→	SessionCount int
   115→
   116→	// SessionIDs contains all session IDs when this is a multi-session checkpoint.
   117→	// The last entry is the most recent session (same as SessionID).
   118→	// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.
   119→	SessionIDs []string
   120→
   121→	// SessionPrompts contains the first prompt for each session (parallel to SessionIDs).
   122→	// Used to display context when showing resume commands for multi-session checkpoints.
   123→	SessionPrompts []string
   124→}
   125→
   126→// RewindPreview describes what will happen when rewinding to a checkpoint.
   127→// Used to warn users about files that will be modified or deleted.
   128→type RewindPreview struct {
   129→	// FilesToRestore are files from the checkpoint that will be written/restored.
   130→	FilesToRestore []string
   131→
   132→	// FilesToDelete are untracked files that will be removed.
   133→	// These are files created after the checkpoint that aren't in the checkpoint tree
   134→	// and weren't present at session start.
   135→	FilesToDelete []string
   136→
   137→	// TrackedChanges are tracked files with uncommitted changes that will be reverted.
   138→	// These come from the existing CanRewind() warning.
   139→	TrackedChanges []string
   140→}
   141→
   142→// SaveContext contains all information needed for saving changes.
   143→// All file paths should be pre-filtered and normalized by the CLI layer.
   144→type SaveContext struct {
   145→	// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier
   146→	SessionID string
   147→
   148→	// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified during the session
   149→	// (extracted from the transcript, already filtered and relative)
   150→	ModifiedFiles []string
   151→
   152→	// NewFiles is the list of new files created during the session
   153→	// (pre-computed by CLI from pre-prompt state comparison)
   154→	NewFiles []string
   155→
   156→	// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted during the session
   157→	// (tracked files that no longer exist)
   158→	DeletedFiles []string
   159→
   160→	// MetadataDir is the path to the session metadata directory
   161→	MetadataDir string
   162→
   163→	// MetadataDirAbs is the absolute path to the session metadata directory
   164→	MetadataDirAbs string
   165→
   166→	// CommitMessage is the generated commit message
   167→	CommitMessage string
   168→
   169→	// TranscriptPath is the path to the transcript file
   170→	TranscriptPath string
   171→
   172→	// AuthorName is the name to use for commits
   173→	AuthorName string
   174→
   175→	// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits
   176→	AuthorEmail string
   177→
   178→	// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., "Claude Code", "Cursor")
   179→	AgentType agent.AgentType
   180→
   181→	// Transcript position at checkpoint start - tracks what was added during this checkpoint
   182→	TranscriptIdentifierAtStart string // Last identifier when checkpoint started (UUID for Claude, message ID for Gemini)
   183→	TranscriptLinesAtStart      int    // Line count when checkpoint started
   184→
   185→	// TokenUsage contains the token usage for this checkpoint
   186→	TokenUsage *agent.TokenUsage
   187→}
   188→
   189→// TaskCheckpointContext contains all information needed for saving a task checkpoint.
   190→// This is called by the PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.
   191→// The strategy is responsible for creating metadata structures and storing them
   192→// according to its storage approach.
   193→type TaskCheckpointContext struct {
   194→	// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier
   195→	SessionID string
   196→
   197→	// ToolUseID is the unique identifier for this Task tool invocation
   198→	ToolUseID string
   199→
   200→	// AgentID is the subagent identifier (from tool_response.agentId)
   201→	AgentID string
   202→
   203→	// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified by the subagent
   204→	// (extracted from the subagent's transcript)
   205→	ModifiedFiles []string
   206→
   207→	// NewFiles is the list of new files created by the subagent
   208→	// (computed from pre-task state comparison)
   209→	NewFiles []string
   210→
   211→	// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted by the subagent
   212→	DeletedFiles []string
   213→
   214→	// TranscriptPath is the path to the main session transcript
   215→	TranscriptPath string
   216→
   217→	// SubagentTranscriptPath is the path to the subagent's transcript (if available)
   218→	SubagentTranscriptPath string
   219→
   220→	// CheckpointUUID is the UUID for transcript truncation when rewinding
   221→	CheckpointUUID string
   222→
   223→	// AuthorName is the name to use for commits
   224→	AuthorName string
   225→
   226→	// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits
   227→	AuthorEmail string
   228→
   229→	// IsIncremental indicates this is an incremental checkpoint during task execution,
   230→	// not a final task completion checkpoint. When true:
   231→	// - Writes to checkpoints/NNN-{tool-use-id}.json instead of checkpoint.json
   232→	// - Skips transcript handling
   233→	// - Uses incremental commit message
   234→	IsIncremental bool
   235→
   236→	// IncrementalSequence is the checkpoint sequence number (1, 2, 3, ...)
   237→	// Only used when IsIncremental is true
   238→	IncrementalSequence int
   239→
   240→	// IncrementalType is the tool that triggered this checkpoint ("TodoWrite", "Edit", etc.)
   241→	// Only used when IsIncremental is true
   242→	IncrementalType string
   243→
   244→	// IncrementalData is the tool_input payload for this checkpoint
   245→	// Only used when IsIncremental is true
   246→	IncrementalData json.RawMessage
   247→
   248→	// SubagentType is the type of subagent (e.g., "dev", "reviewer")
   249→	// Extracted from tool_input.subagent_type in Task tool
   250→	// Used for descriptive commit messages
   251→	SubagentType string
   252→
   253→	// TaskDescription is the task description provided to the subagent
   254→	// Extracted from tool_input.description in Task tool
   255→	// Used for descriptive commit messages
   256→	TaskDescription string
   257→
   258→	// TodoContent is the content of the in-progress todo item
   259→	// Extracted from tool_input.todos where status == "in_progress"
   260→	// Used for descriptive incremental checkpoint messages
   261→	TodoContent string
   262→
   263→	// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., "Claude Code", "Cursor")
   264→	AgentType agent.AgentType
   265→}
   266→
   267→// TaskCheckpoint contains the checkpoint information written to checkpoint.json
   268→type TaskCheckpoint struct {
   269→	SessionID      string `json:"session_id"`
   270→	ToolUseID      string `json:"tool_use_id"`
   271→	CheckpointUUID string `json:"checkpoint_uuid"`
   272→	AgentID        string `json:"agent_id,omitempty"`
   273→}
   274→
   275→// SubagentCheckpoint represents an intermediate checkpoint created during subagent execution.
   276→// These are created by PostToolUse hooks for tools like TodoWrite, Edit, Write.
   277→type SubagentCheckpoint struct {
   278→	Type      string          `json:"type"`        // Tool name: "TodoWrite", "Edit", "Write"
   279→	ToolUseID string          `json:"tool_use_id"` // The tool use ID that created this checkpoint
   280→	Timestamp time.Time       `json:"timestamp"`   // When the checkpoint was created
   281→	Data      json.RawMessage `json:"data"`        // Type-specific payload (tool_input)
   282→}
   283→
   284→// TaskMetadataDir returns the path to a task's metadata directory
   285→// within the session metadata directory.
   286→func TaskMetadataDir(sessionMetadataDir, toolUseID string) string {
   287→	return sessionMetadataDir + "/tasks/" + toolUseID
   288→}
   289→
   290→// ReadTaskCheckpoint reads the checkpoint.json file from a task metadata directory.
   291→// This is used during rewind to get the checkpoint UUID for transcript truncation.
   292→func ReadTaskCheckpoint(taskMetadataDir string) (*TaskCheckpoint, error) {
   293→	checkpointFile := taskMetadataDir + "/checkpoint.json"
   294→
   295→	data, err := os.ReadFile(checkpointFile) //nolint:gosec // Reading from controlled git metadata path
   296→	if err != nil {
   297→		return nil, err
   298→	}
   299→
   300→	var checkpoint TaskCheckpoint
   301→	if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &checkpoint); err != nil {
   302→		return nil, err
   303→	}
   304→
   305→	return &checkpoint, nil
   306→}
   307→
   308→// Strategy defines the interface for git operation strategies.
   309→// Different implementations can use commits, branches, stashes, etc.
   310→//
   311→// Note: State capture (tracking untracked files before a session) is handled
   312→// by the CLI layer, not the strategy. The strategy receives pre-computed
   313→// file lists in SaveContext.
   314→type Strategy interface {
   315→	// Name returns the strategy identifier (e.g., "commit", "branch", "stash")
   316→	Name() string
   317→
   318→	// Description returns a human-readable description for the setup wizard
   319→	Description() string
   320→
   321→	// AllowsMainBranch returns true if this strategy can safely operate on the
   322→	// default branch (main/master). Strategies that don't modify the working
   323→	// branch's commit history (like manual-commit strategies) can return true.
   324→	// Strategies that create commits on the working branch should return false
   325→	// to prevent polluting main branch history.
   326→	AllowsMainBranch() bool
   327→
   328→	// ValidateRepository checks if the repository is in a valid state
   329→	// for this strategy to operate. Returns an error if validation fails.
   330→	ValidateRepository() error
   331→
   332→	// SaveChanges is called on Stop to save all session changes
   333→	// using this strategy's approach (commit, branch, stash, etc.)
   334→	SaveChanges(ctx SaveContext) error
   335→
   336→	// SaveTaskCheckpoint is called by PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.
   337→	// Creates a checkpoint commit with task metadata for later rewind.
   338→	// Different strategies may handle this differently:
   339→	// - Commit strategy: commits to active branch
   340→	// - Manual-commit strategy: commits to shadow branch
   341→	// - Auto-commit strategy: commits logs to shadow only (code deferred to Stop)
   342→	SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx TaskCheckpointContext) error
   343→
   344→	// GetRewindPoints returns available points to rewind to.
   345→	// The limit parameter controls the maximum number of points to return.
   346→	GetRewindPoints(limit int) ([]RewindPoint, error)
   347→
   348→	// Rewind restores the repository to the given rewind point.
   349→	// The metadataDir in the point is used to restore the session transcript.
   350→	Rewind(point RewindPoint) error
   351→
   352→	// CanRewind checks if rewinding is currently possible.
   353→	// Returns (canRewind, reason if not, error)
   354→	CanRewind() (bool, string, error)
   355→
   356→	// PreviewRewind returns what will happen if rewinding to the given point.
   357→	// This allows showing warnings about files that will be deleted before the rewind.
   358→	// Returns nil if preview is not supported (e.g., auto-commit strategy).
   359→	PreviewRewind(point RewindPoint) (*RewindPreview, error)
   360→
   361→	// GetTaskCheckpoint returns the task checkpoint for a given rewind point.
   362→	// For strategies that store checkpoints in git (auto-commit), this reads from the branch.
   363→	// For strategies that store checkpoints on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the filesystem.
   364→	// Returns nil, nil if not a task checkpoint or checkpoint not found.
   365→	GetTaskCheckpoint(point RewindPoint) (*TaskCheckpoint, error)
   366→
   367→	// GetTaskCheckpointTranscript returns the session transcript for a task checkpoint.
   368→	// For strategies that store transcripts in git (auto-commit), this reads from the branch.
   369→	// For strategies that store transcripts on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the filesystem.
   370→	GetTaskCheckpointTranscript(point RewindPoint) ([]byte, error)
   371→
   372→	// GetSessionInfo returns session information for linking commits.
   373→	// This is used by the context command to generate trailers.
   374→	// Returns ErrNoSession if no session info is available.
   375→	GetSessionInfo() (*SessionInfo, error)
   376→
   377→	// EnsureSetup ensures the strategy's required setup is in place,
   378→	// installing any missing pieces (git hooks, gitignore entries, etc.).
   379→	// Returns nil if setup is complete or was successfully installed.
   380→	EnsureSetup() error
   381→
   382→	// NOTE: ListSessions and GetSession are standalone functions in session.go.
   383→	// They read from entire/sessions and merge with SessionSource if implemented.
   384→
   385→	// GetMetadataRef returns a reference to the metadata commit for the given checkpoint.
   386→	// Format: "<branch>@<commit-sha>" (e.g., "entire/sessions@abc123").
   387→	// Returns empty string if not applicable (e.g., commit strategy with filesystem metadata).
   388→	GetMetadataRef(checkpoint Checkpoint) string
   389→
   390→	// GetSessionMetadataRef returns a reference to the most recent metadata commit for a session.
   391→	// Format: "<branch>@<commit-sha>" (e.g., "entire/sessions@abc123").
   392→	// Returns empty string if not applicable or session not found.
   393→	GetSessionMetadataRef(sessionID string) string
   394→
   395→	// GetSessionContext returns the context.md content for a session.
   396→	// Returns empty string if not available.
   397→	GetSessionContext(sessionID string) string
   398→
   399→	// GetCheckpointLog returns the session transcript for a specific checkpoint.
   400→	// For strategies that store transcripts in git branches (auto-commit, manual-commit),
   401→	// this reads from the checkpoint's commit tree.
   402→	// For strategies that store on disk (commit), reads from the filesystem.
   403→	// Returns ErrNoMetadata if transcript is not available.
   404→	GetCheckpointLog(checkpoint Checkpoint) ([]byte, error)
   405→}
   406→
   407→// SessionInitializer is an optional interface for strategies that need to
   408→// initialize session state when a user prompt is submitted.
   409→// Strategies like manual-commit use this to create session state files that
   410→// the git prepare-commit-msg hook can detect.
   411→type SessionInitializer interface {
   412→	// InitializeSession creates session state for a new session.
   413→	// Called during UserPromptSubmit hook before any checkpoints are created.
   414→	// agentType is the human-readable name of the agent (e.g., "Claude Code").
   415→	// transcriptPath is the path to the live transcript file (for mid-session commit detection).
   416→	InitializeSession(sessionID string, agentType agent.AgentType, transcriptPath string) error
   417→}
   418→
   419→// PrepareCommitMsgHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to
   420→// handle the git prepare-commit-msg hook.
   421→type PrepareCommitMsgHandler interface {
   422→	// PrepareCommitMsg is called by the git prepare-commit-msg hook.
   423→	// It can modify the commit message file to add trailers, etc.
   424→	// The source parameter indicates how the commit was initiated:
   425→	//   - "" or "template": normal editor flow
   426→	//   - "message": using -m or -F flag
   427→	//   - "merge": merge commit
   428→	//   - "squash": squash merge
   429→	//   - "commit": amend with -c/-C
   430→	// Should return nil on errors to not block commits (log warnings to stderr).
   431→	PrepareCommitMsg(commitMsgFile string, source string) error
   432→}
   433→
   434→// PostCommitHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to
   435→// handle the git post-commit hook.
   436→type PostCommitHandler interface {
   437→	// PostCommit is called by the git post-commit hook after a commit is created.
   438→	// Used to perform actions like condensing session data after commits.
   439→	// Should return nil on errors to not block subsequent operations (log warnings to stderr).
   440→	PostCommit() error
   441→}
   442→
   443→// CommitMsgHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to
   444→// handle the git commit-msg hook.
   445→type CommitMsgHandler interface {
   446→	// CommitMsg is called by the git commit-msg hook after the user edits the message.
   447→	// Used to validate or modify the final commit message before the commit is created.
   448→	// If this returns an error, the commit is aborted.
   449→	CommitMsg(commitMsgFile string) error
   450→}
   451→
   452→// PrePushHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to
   453→// handle the git pre-push hook.
   454→type PrePushHandler interface {
   455→	// PrePush is called by the git pre-push hook before pushing to a remote.
   456→	// Used to push session branches (e.g., entire/sessions) alongside user pushes.
   457→	// The remote parameter is the name of the remote being pushed to.
   458→	// Should return nil on errors to not block pushes (log warnings to stderr).
   459→	PrePush(remote string) error
   460→}
   461→
   462→// LogsOnlyRestorer is an optional interface for strategies that support
   463→// restoring session logs without file state restoration.
   464→// This is used for "logs-only" rewind points where only the session transcript
   465→// can be restored (file state requires git checkout).
   466→type LogsOnlyRestorer interface {
   467→	// RestoreLogsOnly restores session logs from a logs-only rewind point.
   468→	// Does not modify the working directory - only restores the transcript
   469→	// to Claude's project directory.
   470→	// If force is false, prompts for confirmation when local logs have newer timestamps.
   471→	RestoreLogsOnly(point RewindPoint, force bool) error
   472→}
   473→
   474→// SessionResetter is an optional interface for strategies that support
   475→// resetting session state and shadow branches.
   476→// This is used by the "rewind reset" command to clean up shadow branches
   477→// and session state when a user wants to start fresh.
   478→type SessionResetter interface {
   479→	// Reset deletes the shadow branch and session state for the current HEAD.
   480→	// Returns nil if there's nothing to reset (no shadow branch).
   481→	Reset() error
   482→}
   483→
   484→// ConcurrentSessionChecker is an optional interface for strategies that support
   485→// counting concurrent sessions with uncommitted changes.
   486→// This is used by the SessionStart hook to show an informational message about
   487→// how many other active conversations will be included in the next commit.
   488→type ConcurrentSessionChecker interface {
   489→	// CountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints returns the number of other active sessions
   490→	// with uncommitted checkpoints on the same base commit.
   491→	// Returns 0, nil if no such sessions exist.
   492→	CountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints(currentSessionID string) (int, error)
   493→}
   494→
   495→// SessionSource is an optional interface for strategies that provide additional
   496→// sessions beyond those stored on the entire/sessions branch.
   497→// For example, manual-commit strategy provides active sessions from .git/entire-sessions/
   498→// that haven't yet been condensed to entire/sessions.
   499→//
   500→// ListSessions() automatically discovers all registered strategies, checks if they
   501→// implement SessionSource, and merges their additional sessions by ID.
   502→type SessionSource interface {
   503→	// GetAdditionalSessions returns sessions not yet on entire/sessions branch.
   504→	GetAdditionalSessions() ([]*Session, error)
   505→}
   506→
   507→// OrphanedItemsLister is an optional interface for strategies that can identify
   508→// orphaned items (shadow branches, session states, checkpoints) that should be
   509→// cleaned up. This is used by the "entire session cleanup" command.
   510→//
   511→// ListAllCleanupItems() automatically discovers all registered strategies, checks
   512→// if they implement OrphanedItemsLister, and combines their orphaned items.
   513→type OrphanedItemsLister interface {

   515→	// Each strategy defines what "orphaned" means for its own data structures.
   516→	ListOrphanedItems() ([]CleanupItem, error)
   517→}

1→package agent
     2→
     3→import (
     4→	"fmt"
     5→	"slices"
     6→	"sync"
     7→)
     8→
     9→var (
    10→	registryMu sync.RWMutex
    11→	registry   = make(map[AgentName]Factory)
    12→)
    13→
    14→// Factory creates a new agent instance
    15→type Factory func() Agent
    16→
    17→// Register adds an agent factory to the registry.
    18→// Called from init() in each agent implementation.
    19→func Register(name AgentName, factory Factory) {
    20→	registryMu.Lock()
    21→	defer registryMu.Unlock()
    22→	registry[name] = factory
    23→}
    24→
    25→// Get retrieves an agent by name.
    26→//
    27→
    28→func Get(name AgentName) (Agent, error) {
    29→	registryMu.RLock()
    30→	defer registryMu.RUnlock()
    31→
    32→	factory, ok := registry[name]
    33→	if !ok {
    34→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("unknown agent: %s (available: %v)", name, List())
    35→	}
    36→	return factory(), nil
    37→}
    38→
    39→// List returns all registered agent names in sorted order.
    40→func List() []AgentName {
    41→	registryMu.RLock()
    42→	defer registryMu.RUnlock()
    43→
    44→	names := make([]AgentName, 0, len(registry))
    45→	for name := range registry {
    46→		names = append(names, name)
    47→	}
    48→	slices.Sort(names)
    49→	return names
    50→}
    51→
    52→// Detect attempts to auto-detect which agent is being used.
    53→// Checks each registered agent's DetectPresence method.
    54→//
    55→
    56→func Detect() (Agent, error) {
    57→	registryMu.RLock()
    58→	defer registryMu.RUnlock()
    59→
    60→	for _, factory := range registry {
    61→		ag := factory()
    62→		if present, err := ag.DetectPresence(); err == nil && present {
    63→			return ag, nil
    64→		}
    65→	}
    66→	return nil, fmt.Errorf("no agent detected (available: %v)", List())
    67→}
    68→
    69→// AgentName is the registry key type for agents (e.g., "claude-code", "gemini").
    70→//
    71→//nolint:revive // stuttering is intentional - distinguishes from AgentType when both are used
    72→type AgentName string
    73→
    74→// AgentType is the display name type stored in metadata/trailers (e.g., "Claude Code", "Gemini CLI").
    75→//
    76→//nolint:revive // stuttering is intentional - distinguishes from AgentName when both are used
    77→type AgentType string
    78→
    79→// Agent name constants (registry keys)
    80→const (
    81→	AgentNameClaudeCode AgentName = "claude-code"
    82→	AgentNameGemini     AgentName = "gemini"
    83→)
    84→
    85→// Agent type constants (type identifiers stored in metadata/trailers)
    86→const (
    87→	AgentTypeClaudeCode AgentType = "Claude Code"
    88→	AgentTypeGemini     AgentType = "Gemini CLI"
    89→	AgentTypeUnknown    AgentType = "Agent" // Fallback for backwards compatibility
    90→)
    91→
    92→// DefaultAgentName is the registry key for the default agent.
    93→const DefaultAgentName AgentName = AgentNameClaudeCode
    94→
    95→// GetByAgentType retrieves an agent by its type identifier.
    96→//
    97→// Note: This uses a linear search that instantiates agents until a match is found.
    98→// This is acceptable because:
    99→//   - Agent count is small (~2-20 agents)
   100→//   - Agent factories are lightweight (empty struct allocation)
   101→//   - Called infrequently (commit hooks, rewind, debug commands - not hot paths)
   102→//   - Cost is ~400ns worst case vs milliseconds for I/O operations
   103→//
   104→// Only optimize if agent count exceeds 100 or profiling shows this as a bottleneck.
   105→func GetByAgentType(agentType AgentType) (Agent, error) {
   106→	registryMu.RLock()
   107→	defer registryMu.RUnlock()
   108→
   109→	for _, factory := range registry {
   110→		ag := factory()
   111→		if ag.Type() == agentType {
   112→			return ag, nil
   113→		}
   114→	}
   115→
   116→	return nil, fmt.Errorf("unknown agent type: %s", agentType)
   117→}
   118→
   119→// Default returns the default agent.
   120→// Returns nil if the default agent is not registered.
   121→//
   122→//nolint:ireturn,errcheck // Factory pattern returns interface; error is acceptable to ignore for default
   123→func Default() Agent {
   124→	a, _ := Get(DefaultAgentName)
   125→	return a
   126→}
   127→

1→// Package trailers provides parsing and formatting for Entire commit message trailers.
     2→// Trailers are key-value metadata appended to git commit messages following the
     3→// git trailer convention (key: value format after a blank line).
     4→package trailers
     5→
     6→import (
     7→	"fmt"
     8→	"regexp"
     9→	"strings"
    10→
    11→	checkpointID "github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id"
    12→)
    13→
    14→// Trailer key constants used in commit messages.
    15→const (
    16→	// MetadataTrailerKey points to the metadata directory within a commit tree.
    17→	MetadataTrailerKey = "Entire-Metadata"
    18→
    19→	// MetadataTaskTrailerKey points to the task metadata directory for subagent checkpoints.
    20→	MetadataTaskTrailerKey = "Entire-Metadata-Task"
    21→
    22→	// StrategyTrailerKey indicates which strategy created the commit.
    23→	StrategyTrailerKey = "Entire-Strategy"
    24→
    25→	// BaseCommitTrailerKey links shadow commits to their base code commit.
    26→	BaseCommitTrailerKey = "Base-Commit"
    27→
    28→	// SessionTrailerKey identifies which session created a commit.
    29→	SessionTrailerKey = "Entire-Session"
    30→
    31→	// CondensationTrailerKey identifies the condensation ID for a commit (legacy).
    32→	CondensationTrailerKey = "Entire-Condensation"
    33→
    34→	// SourceRefTrailerKey links code commits to their metadata on a shadow/metadata branch.
    35→	// Format: "<branch>@<commit-hash>" e.g. "entire/metadata@abc123def456"
    36→	SourceRefTrailerKey = "Entire-Source-Ref"
    37→
    38→	// CheckpointTrailerKey links commits to their checkpoint metadata on entire/sessions.
    39→	// Format: 12 hex characters e.g. "a3b2c4d5e6f7"
    40→	// This trailer survives git amend and rebase operations.
    41→	CheckpointTrailerKey = "Entire-Checkpoint"
    42→
    43→	// EphemeralBranchTrailerKey identifies the shadow branch that a checkpoint originated from.
    44→	// Used in manual-commit strategy checkpoint commits on entire/sessions branch.
    45→	// Format: full branch name e.g. "entire/2b4c177"
    46→	EphemeralBranchTrailerKey = "Ephemeral-branch"
    47→
    48→	// AgentTrailerKey identifies the agent that created a checkpoint.
    49→	// Format: human-readable agent name e.g. "Claude Code", "Cursor"
    50→	AgentTrailerKey = "Entire-Agent"
    51→)
    52→
    53→// Pre-compiled regexes for trailer parsing.
    54→var (
    55→	// Trailer parsing regexes.
    56→	strategyTrailerRegex     = regexp.MustCompile(StrategyTrailerKey + `:\s*(.+)`)
    57→	metadataTrailerRegex     = regexp.MustCompile(MetadataTrailerKey + `:\s*(.+)`)
    58→	taskMetadataTrailerRegex = regexp.MustCompile(MetadataTaskTrailerKey + `:\s*(.+)`)
    59→	baseCommitTrailerRegex   = regexp.MustCompile(BaseCommitTrailerKey + `:\s*([a-f0-9]{40})`)
    60→	condensationTrailerRegex = regexp.MustCompile(CondensationTrailerKey + `:\s*(.+)`)
    61→	sessionTrailerRegex      = regexp.MustCompile(SessionTrailerKey + `:\s*(.+)`)
    62→	checkpointTrailerRegex   = regexp.MustCompile(CheckpointTrailerKey + `:\s*(` + checkpointID.Pattern + `)(?:\s|$)`)
    63→)
    64→
    65→// ParseStrategy extracts strategy from commit message.
    66→// Returns the strategy name and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.
    67→func ParseStrategy(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {
    68→	matches := strategyTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
    69→	if len(matches) > 1 {
    70→		return strings.TrimSpace(matches[1]), true
    71→	}
    72→	return "", false
    73→}
    74→
    75→// ParseMetadata extracts metadata dir from commit message.
    76→// Returns the metadata directory and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.
    77→func ParseMetadata(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {
    78→	matches := metadataTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
    79→	if len(matches) > 1 {
    80→		return strings.TrimSpace(matches[1]), true
    81→	}
    82→	return "", false
    83→}
    84→
    85→// ParseTaskMetadata extracts task metadata dir from commit message.
    86→// Returns the task metadata directory and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.
    87→func ParseTaskMetadata(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {
    88→	matches := taskMetadataTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
    89→	if len(matches) > 1 {
    90→		return strings.TrimSpace(matches[1]), true
    91→	}
    92→	return "", false
    93→}
    94→
    95→// ParseBaseCommit extracts the base commit SHA from a commit message.
    96→// Returns the full SHA and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.
    97→func ParseBaseCommit(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {
    98→	matches := baseCommitTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
    99→	if len(matches) > 1 {
   100→		return matches[1], true
   101→	}
   102→	return "", false
   103→}
   104→
   105→// ParseCondensation extracts the condensation ID from a commit message.
   106→// Returns the condensation ID and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.
   107→func ParseCondensation(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {
   108→	matches := condensationTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
   109→	if len(matches) > 1 {
   110→		return strings.TrimSpace(matches[1]), true
   111→	}
   112→	return "", false
   113→}
   114→
   115→// ParseSession extracts the session ID from a commit message.
   116→// Returns the session ID and true if found, empty string and false otherwise.
   117→// Note: If multiple Entire-Session trailers exist, this returns only the first one.
   118→// Use ParseAllSessions to get all session IDs.
   119→func ParseSession(commitMessage string) (string, bool) {
   120→	matches := sessionTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
   121→	if len(matches) > 1 {
   122→		return strings.TrimSpace(matches[1]), true
   123→	}
   124→	return "", false
   125→}
   126→
   127→// ParseCheckpoint extracts the checkpoint ID from a commit message.
   128→// Returns the CheckpointID and true if found, empty ID and false otherwise.
   129→func ParseCheckpoint(commitMessage string) (checkpointID.CheckpointID, bool) {
   130→	matches := checkpointTrailerRegex.FindStringSubmatch(commitMessage)
   131→	if len(matches) > 1 {
   132→		idStr := strings.TrimSpace(matches[1])
   133→		// Validate it's a proper checkpoint ID
   134→		if cpID, err := checkpointID.NewCheckpointID(idStr); err == nil {
   135→			return cpID, true
   136→		}
   137→	}
   138→	return checkpointID.EmptyCheckpointID, false
   139→}
   140→
   141→// ParseAllSessions extracts all session IDs from a commit message.
   142→// Returns a slice of session IDs (may be empty if none found).
   143→// Duplicate session IDs are deduplicated while preserving order.
   144→// This is useful for commits that may have multiple Entire-Session trailers.
   145→func ParseAllSessions(commitMessage string) []string {
   146→	matches := sessionTrailerRegex.FindAllStringSubmatch(commitMessage, -1)
   147→	if len(matches) == 0 {
   148→		return nil
   149→	}
   150→
   151→	seen := make(map[string]bool)
   152→	sessionIDs := make([]string, 0, len(matches))
   153→	for _, match := range matches {
   154→		if len(match) > 1 {
   155→			sessionID := strings.TrimSpace(match[1])
   156→			if !seen[sessionID] {
   157→				seen[sessionID] = true
   158→				sessionIDs = append(sessionIDs, sessionID)
   159→			}
   160→		}
   161→	}
   162→	return sessionIDs
   163→}
   164→
   165→// FormatStrategy creates a commit message with just the strategy trailer.
   166→func FormatStrategy(message, strategy string) string {
   167→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s\n\n%s: %s\n", message, StrategyTrailerKey, strategy)
   168→}
   169→
   170→// FormatTaskMetadata creates a commit message with task metadata trailer.
   171→func FormatTaskMetadata(message, taskMetadataDir string) string {
   172→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s\n\n%s: %s\n", message, MetadataTaskTrailerKey, taskMetadataDir)
   173→}
   174→
   175→// FormatTaskMetadataWithStrategy creates a commit message with task metadata and strategy trailers.
   176→func FormatTaskMetadataWithStrategy(message, taskMetadataDir, strategy string) string {
   177→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s\n\n%s: %s\n%s: %s\n", message, MetadataTaskTrailerKey, taskMetadataDir, StrategyTrailerKey, strategy)
   178→}
   179→
   180→// FormatSourceRef creates a formatted source ref string for the trailer.
   181→// Format: "<branch>@<commit-hash-prefix>" (hash truncated to 12 chars)
   182→func FormatSourceRef(branch, commitHash string) string {
   183→	shortHash := commitHash
   184→	if len(shortHash) > 12 {
   185→		shortHash = shortHash[:12]
   186→	}
   187→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s@%s", branch, shortHash)
   188→}
   189→
   190→// FormatMetadata creates a commit message with metadata trailer.
   191→func FormatMetadata(message, metadataDir string) string {
   192→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s\n\n%s: %s\n", message, MetadataTrailerKey, metadataDir)
   193→}
   194→
   195→// FormatMetadataWithStrategy creates a commit message with metadata and strategy trailers.
   196→func FormatMetadataWithStrategy(message, metadataDir, strategy string) string {
   197→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s\n\n%s: %s\n%s: %s\n", message, MetadataTrailerKey, metadataDir, StrategyTrailerKey, strategy)
   198→}
   199→
   200→// FormatShadowCommit creates a commit message for manual-commit strategy checkpoints.
   201→// Includes Entire-Metadata, Entire-Session, and Entire-Strategy trailers.
   202→func FormatShadowCommit(message, metadataDir, sessionID string) string {
   203→	var sb strings.Builder
   204→	sb.WriteString(message)
   205→	sb.WriteString("\n\n")
   206→	sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", MetadataTrailerKey, metadataDir))
   207→	sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", SessionTrailerKey, sessionID))
   208→	sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", StrategyTrailerKey, "manual-commit"))
   209→	return sb.String()
   210→}
   211→
   212→// FormatShadowTaskCommit creates a commit message for manual-commit task checkpoints.
   213→// Includes Entire-Metadata-Task, Entire-Session, and Entire-Strategy trailers.
   214→func FormatShadowTaskCommit(message, taskMetadataDir, sessionID string) string {
   215→	var sb strings.Builder
   216→	sb.WriteString(message)
   217→	sb.WriteString("\n\n")
   218→	sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", MetadataTaskTrailerKey, taskMetadataDir))
   219→	sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", SessionTrailerKey, sessionID))
   220→	sb.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", StrategyTrailerKey, "manual-commit"))
   221→	return sb.String()
   222→}
   223→
   224→// FormatCheckpoint creates a commit message with a checkpoint trailer.
   225→// This links user commits to their checkpoint metadata on entire/sessions branch.
   226→func FormatCheckpoint(message string, cpID checkpointID.CheckpointID) string {
   227→	return fmt.Sprintf("%s\n\n%s: %s\n", message, CheckpointTrailerKey, cpID.String())
   228→}
   229→

1→package strategy
     2→
     3→import (
     4→	"context"
     5→	"fmt"
     6→	"log/slog"
     7→	"os"
     8→	"path/filepath"
     9→	"sort"
    10→
    11→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent"
    12→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint"
    13→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging"
    14→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths"
    15→	"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers"
    16→
    17→	"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5"
    18→	"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing"
    19→)
    20→
    21→// SaveChanges saves a checkpoint to the shadow branch.
    22→// Uses checkpoint.GitStore.WriteTemporary for git operations.
    23→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) SaveChanges(ctx SaveContext) error {
    24→	repo, err := OpenRepository()
    25→	if err != nil {
    26→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to open git repository: %w", err)
    27→	}
    28→
    29→	// Extract session ID from metadata dir
    30→	sessionID := filepath.Base(ctx.MetadataDir)
    31→
    32→	// Load or initialize session state
    33→	state, err := s.loadSessionState(sessionID)
    34→	if err != nil {
    35→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to load session state: %w", err)
    36→	}
    37→	// Initialize if state is nil OR BaseCommit is empty (can happen with partial state from warnings)
    38→	if state == nil || state.BaseCommit == "" {
    39→		// Preserve existing AgentType if we have a partial state, otherwise use default
    40→		agentType := DefaultAgentType
    41→		if state != nil && state.AgentType != "" {
    42→			agentType = state.AgentType
    43→		}
    44→		state, err = s.initializeSession(repo, sessionID, agentType, "") // No transcript path in fallback
    45→		if err != nil {
    46→			return fmt.Errorf("failed to initialize session: %w", err)
    47→		}
    48→	}
    49→
    50→	// Check if HEAD has changed (e.g., Claude did a rebase via tool call) and migrate if needed
    51→	if err := s.migrateAndPersistIfNeeded(repo, state); err != nil {
    52→		return err
    53→	}
    54→
    55→	// Get checkpoint store
    56→	store, err := s.getCheckpointStore()
    57→	if err != nil {
    58→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get checkpoint store: %w", err)
    59→	}

   166→// SaveTaskCheckpoint saves a task checkpoint to the shadow branch.
   167→// Uses checkpoint.GitStore.WriteTemporaryTask for git operations.
   168→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx TaskCheckpointContext) error {
   169→	repo, err := OpenRepository()
   170→	if err != nil {
   171→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to open git repository: %w", err)
   172→	}
   173→
   174→	// Load session state
   175→	state, err := s.loadSessionState(ctx.SessionID)

   179→		agentType := DefaultAgentType
   180→		if state != nil && state.AgentType != "" {
   181→			agentType = state.AgentType
   182→		}
   183→		state, err = s.initializeSession(repo, ctx.SessionID, agentType, "") // No transcript path in fallback
   184→		if err != nil {
   185→			return fmt.Errorf("failed to initialize session for task checkpoint: %w", err)
   186→		}
   187→	}

   204→	// Compute metadata paths for commit message
   205→	sessionMetadataDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(ctx.SessionID)
   206→	taskMetadataDir := TaskMetadataDir(sessionMetadataDir, ctx.ToolUseID)
   207→
   208→	// Generate commit message
   209→	shortToolUseID := ctx.ToolUseID

   213→
   214→	var messageSubject string

   236→		BaseCommit:             state.BaseCommit,
   237→		WorktreeID:             state.WorktreeID,
   238→		ToolUseID:              ctx.ToolUseID,
   239→		AgentID:                ctx.AgentID,
   240→		ModifiedFiles:          ctx.ModifiedFiles,
   241→		NewFiles:               ctx.NewFiles,
   242→		DeletedFiles:           ctx.DeletedFiles,
   243→		TranscriptPath:         ctx.TranscriptPath,
   244→		SubagentTranscriptPath: ctx.SubagentTranscriptPath,
   245→		CheckpointUUID:         ctx.CheckpointUUID,
   246→		CommitMessage:          commitMsg,
   247→		AuthorName:             ctx.AuthorName,
   248→		AuthorEmail:            ctx.AuthorEmail,
   249→		IsIncremental:          ctx.IsIncremental,
   250→		IncrementalSequence:    ctx.IncrementalSequence,
   251→		IncrementalType:        ctx.IncrementalType,
   252→		IncrementalData:        ctx.IncrementalData,
   253→	})

1→// hooks_claudecode_handlers.go contains Claude Code specific hook handler implementations.
     2→// These are called by the hook registry in hook_registry.go.
     3→package cli

     6→	"context"

    19→)
    20→
    21→// hookInputData contains parsed hook input and session identifiers.
    22→type hookInputData struct {
    23→	agent     agent.Agent
    24→	input     *agent.HookInput
    25→	sessionID string
    26→}
    27→
    28→// parseAndLogHookInput parses the hook input and sets up logging context.
    29→func parseAndLogHookInput() (*hookInputData, error) {
    30→	// Get the agent from the hook command context (e.g., "entire hooks claude-code ...")
    31→	ag, err := GetCurrentHookAgent()
    32→	if err != nil {
    33→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to get agent: %w", err)
    34→	}
    35→
    36→	// Parse hook input using agent interface
    37→	input, err := ag.ParseHookInput(agent.HookUserPromptSubmit, os.Stdin)
    38→	if err != nil {
    39→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to parse hook input: %w", err)
    40→	}
    41→
    42→	logCtx := logging.WithAgent(logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), "hooks"), ag.Name())
    43→	logging.Info(logCtx, "user-prompt-submit",
    44→		slog.String("hook", "user-prompt-submit"),
    45→		slog.String("hook_type", "agent"),
    46→		slog.String("model_session_id", input.SessionID),
    47→		slog.String("transcript_path", input.SessionRef),
    48→	)
    49→
    50→	sessionID := input.SessionID
    51→	if sessionID == "" {
    52→		sessionID = unknownSessionID
    53→	}
    54→
    55→	// Get the Entire session ID, preferring the persisted value to handle midnight boundary
    56→	return &hookInputData{
    57→		agent:     ag,
    58→		input:     input,
    59→		sessionID: sessionID,
    60→	}, nil
    61→}
    62→
    63→// captureInitialState captures the initial state on user prompt submit.
    64→func captureInitialState() error {
    65→	// Parse hook input and setup logging
    66→	hookData, err := parseAndLogHookInput()
    67→	if err != nil {
    68→		return err
    69→	}
    70→
    71→	// CLI captures state directly (including transcript position)
    72→	if err := CapturePrePromptState(hookData.sessionID, hookData.input.SessionRef); err != nil {
    73→		return err
    74→	}
    75→
    76→	// If strategy implements SessionInitializer, call it to initialize session state
    77→	strat := GetStrategy()
    78→	if initializer, ok := strat.(strategy.SessionInitializer); ok {
    79→		agentType := hookData.agent.Type()
    80→		if err := initializer.InitializeSession(hookData.sessionID, agentType, hookData.input.SessionRef); err != nil {
    81→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to initialize session state: %v\n", err)
    82→		}
    83→	}
    84→
    85→	return nil
    86→}

    88→// commitWithMetadata commits the session changes with metadata.
    89→func commitWithMetadata() error {

    91→	if skip, branchName := ShouldSkipOnDefaultBranchForStrategy(); skip {

   114→	)
   115→
   116→	sessionID := input.SessionID
   117→	if sessionID == "" {
   118→		sessionID = unknownSessionID
   119→	}
   120→
   121→	transcriptPath := input.SessionRef
   122→	if transcriptPath == "" || !fileExists(transcriptPath) {
   123→		return fmt.Errorf("transcript file not found or empty: %s", transcriptPath)
   124→	}
   125→
   126→	// Create session metadata folder using the entire session ID (preserves original date on resume)
   127→	// Use AbsPath to ensure we create at repo root, not relative to cwd
   128→	sessionDir := paths.SessionMetadataDirFromSessionID(sessionID)
   129→	sessionDirAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(sessionDir)
   130→	if err != nil {
   131→		sessionDirAbs = sessionDir // Fallback to relative
   132→	}
   133→	if err := os.MkdirAll(sessionDirAbs, 0o750); err != nil {
   134→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to create session directory: %w", err)
   135→	}
   136→
   137→	// Copy transcript
   138→	logFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.TranscriptFileName)
   139→	if err := copyFile(transcriptPath, logFile); err != nil {
   140→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to copy transcript: %w", err)
   141→	}
   142→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Copied transcript to: %s\n", sessionDir+"/"+paths.TranscriptFileName)
   143→
   144→	// Load session state to get transcript offset (for strategies that track it)
   145→	// This is used to only parse NEW transcript lines since the last checkpoint
   146→	var transcriptOffset int
   147→	sessionState, loadErr := strategy.LoadSessionState(sessionID)
   148→	if loadErr != nil {
   149→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to load session state: %v\n", loadErr)
   150→	}
   151→	if sessionState != nil {
   152→		transcriptOffset = sessionState.CondensedTranscriptLines
   153→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Session state found: parsing transcript from line %d\n", transcriptOffset)
   154→	}
   155→
   156→	// Parse transcript (optionally from offset for strategies that track transcript position)
   157→	// When transcriptOffset > 0, only parse NEW lines since the last checkpoint
   158→	var transcript []transcriptLine
   159→	var totalLines int
   160→	if transcriptOffset > 0 {
   161→		// Parse only NEW lines since last checkpoint
   162→		transcript, totalLines, err = parseTranscriptFromLine(transcriptPath, transcriptOffset)
   163→		if err != nil {
   164→			return fmt.Errorf("failed to parse transcript from line %d: %w", transcriptOffset, err)
   165→		}
   166→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Parsed %d new transcript lines (total: %d)\n", len(transcript), totalLines)
   167→	} else {
   168→		// First prompt or no session state - parse entire transcript
   169→		// Use parseTranscriptFromLine with offset 0 to also get totalLines
   170→		transcript, totalLines, err = parseTranscriptFromLine(transcriptPath, 0)
   171→		if err != nil {
   172→			return fmt.Errorf("failed to parse transcript: %w", err)
   173→		}
   174→	}
   175→
   176→	// Extract all prompts since last checkpoint for prompt file
   177→	allPrompts := extractUserPrompts(transcript)
   178→	promptFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.PromptFileName)
   179→	promptContent := strings.Join(allPrompts, "\n\n---\n\n")
   180→	if err := os.WriteFile(promptFile, []byte(promptContent), 0o600); err != nil {
   181→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to write prompt file: %w", err)
   182→	}
   183→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Extracted %d prompt(s) to: %s\n", len(allPrompts), sessionDir+"/"+paths.PromptFileName)
   184→
   185→	// Extract summary
   186→	summaryFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.SummaryFileName)
   187→	summary := extractLastAssistantMessage(transcript)
   188→	if err := os.WriteFile(summaryFile, []byte(summary), 0o600); err != nil {
   189→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to write summary file: %w", err)
   190→	}
   191→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Extracted summary to: %s\n", sessionDir+"/"+paths.SummaryFileName)
   192→
   193→	// Get modified files from transcript
   194→	modifiedFiles := extractModifiedFiles(transcript)
   195→
   196→	// Generate commit message from last user prompt
   197→	lastPrompt := ""
   198→	if len(allPrompts) > 0 {
   199→		lastPrompt = allPrompts[len(allPrompts)-1]
   200→	}
   201→	commitMessage := generateCommitMessage(lastPrompt)
   202→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Using commit message: %s\n", commitMessage)
   203→
   204→	// Get repo root for path conversion (not cwd, since Claude may be in a subdirectory)
   205→	// Using cwd would filter out files in sibling directories (paths starting with ..)
   206→	repoRoot, err := paths.RepoRoot()
   207→	if err != nil {
   208→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get repo root: %w", err)
   209→	}
   210→
   211→	// Load pre-prompt state (captured on UserPromptSubmit)
   212→	preState, err := LoadPrePromptState(sessionID)
   213→	if err != nil {
   214→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to load pre-prompt state: %v\n", err)
   215→	}
   216→	if preState != nil {
   217→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Loaded pre-prompt state: %d pre-existing untracked files\n", len(preState.UntrackedFiles))
   218→	}
   219→
   220→	// Compute new and deleted files (single git status call)
   221→	newFiles, deletedFiles, err := ComputeFileChanges(preState)
   222→	if err != nil {
   223→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to compute file changes: %v\n", err)
   224→	}
   225→
   226→	// Filter and normalize all paths (CLI responsibility)
   227→	relModifiedFiles := FilterAndNormalizePaths(modifiedFiles, repoRoot)
   228→	relNewFiles := FilterAndNormalizePaths(newFiles, repoRoot)
   229→	relDeletedFiles := FilterAndNormalizePaths(deletedFiles, repoRoot)
   230→
   231→	// Check if there are any changes to commit
   232→	totalChanges := len(relModifiedFiles) + len(relNewFiles) + len(relDeletedFiles)
   233→	if totalChanges == 0 {
   234→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "No files were modified during this session\n")
   235→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Skipping commit\n")
   236→		// Clean up state even when skipping
   237→		if err := CleanupPrePromptState(sessionID); err != nil {
   238→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to cleanup pre-prompt state: %v\n", err)
   239→		}
   240→		return nil
   241→	}
   242→
   243→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Files modified during session (%d):\n", len(relModifiedFiles))
   244→	for _, file := range relModifiedFiles {
   245→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "  - %s\n", file)
   246→	}
   247→	if len(relNewFiles) > 0 {
   248→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "New files created (%d):\n", len(relNewFiles))
   249→		for _, file := range relNewFiles {
   250→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "  + %s\n", file)
   251→		}
   252→	}
   253→	if len(relDeletedFiles) > 0 {
   254→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Files deleted (%d):\n", len(relDeletedFiles))
   255→		for _, file := range relDeletedFiles {
   256→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "  - %s\n", file)
   257→		}
   258→	}
   259→
   260→	// Create context file before saving changes
   261→	contextFile := filepath.Join(sessionDirAbs, paths.ContextFileName)
   262→	if err := createContextFileMinimal(contextFile, commitMessage, sessionID, promptFile, summaryFile, transcript); err != nil {
   263→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to create context file: %w", err)
   264→	}
   265→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Created context file: %s\n", sessionDir+"/"+paths.ContextFileName)
   266→
   267→	// Get git author from local/global config
   268→	author, err := GetGitAuthor()
   269→	if err != nil {
   270→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get git author: %w", err)
   271→	}
   272→
   273→	// Get the configured strategy
   274→	strat := GetStrategy()
   275→
   276→	// Ensure strategy setup is in place (auto-installs git hook, gitignore, etc. if needed)
   277→	if err := strat.EnsureSetup(); err != nil {
   278→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to ensure strategy setup: %v\n", err)
   279→	}
   280→
   281→	// Get agent type from the currently executing hook agent (authoritative source)
   282→	var agentType agent.AgentType
   283→	if hookAgent, agentErr := GetCurrentHookAgent(); agentErr == nil {
   284→		agentType = hookAgent.Type()
   285→	}
   286→
   287→	// Get transcript position from pre-prompt state (captured at checkpoint start)
   288→	var transcriptIdentifierAtStart string
   289→	var transcriptLinesAtStart int
   290→	if preState != nil {
   291→		transcriptIdentifierAtStart = preState.LastTranscriptIdentifier
   292→		transcriptLinesAtStart = preState.LastTranscriptLineCount
   293→	}
   294→
   295→	// Calculate token usage for this checkpoint (Claude Code specific)
   296→	var tokenUsage *agent.TokenUsage
   297→	if transcriptPath != "" {
   298→		// Subagents are stored in a subagents/ directory next to the main transcript
   299→		subagentsDir := filepath.Join(filepath.Dir(transcriptPath), sessionID, "subagents")
   300→		usage, err := claudecode.CalculateTotalTokenUsage(transcriptPath, transcriptLinesAtStart, subagentsDir)
   301→		if err != nil {
   302→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to calculate token usage: %v\n", err)
   303→		} else {
   304→			tokenUsage = usage
   305→		}
   306→	}
   307→
   308→	// Build fully-populated save context and delegate to strategy
   309→	ctx := strategy.SaveContext{
   310→		SessionID:                   sessionID,
   311→		ModifiedFiles:               relModifiedFiles,
   312→		NewFiles:                    relNewFiles,
   313→		DeletedFiles:                relDeletedFiles,
   314→		MetadataDir:                 sessionDir,
   315→		MetadataDirAbs:              sessionDirAbs,
   316→		CommitMessage:               commitMessage,
   317→		TranscriptPath:              transcriptPath,
   318→		AuthorName:                  author.Name,
   319→		AuthorEmail:                 author.Email,
   320→		AgentType:                   agentType,
   321→		TranscriptIdentifierAtStart: transcriptIdentifierAtStart,
   322→		TranscriptLinesAtStart:      transcriptLinesAtStart,
   323→		TokenUsage:                  tokenUsage,
   324→	}
   325→
   326→	if err := strat.SaveChanges(ctx); err != nil {
   327→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to save changes: %w", err)
   328→	}
   329→
   330→	// Update session state with new transcript position for strategies that create
   331→	// commits on the active branch (auto-commit strategy). This prevents parsing old transcript
   332→	// lines on subsequent checkpoints.
   333→	// Note: Shadow strategy doesn't create commits on the active branch, so its
   334→	// checkpoints don't "consume" the transcript in the same way. Shadow should
   335→	// continue parsing the full transcript to capture all files touched in the session.
   336→	if strat.Name() == strategy.StrategyNameAutoCommit {
   337→		// Create session state lazily if it doesn't exist (backward compat for resumed sessions
   338→		// or if InitializeSession was never called/failed)
   339→		if sessionState == nil {
   340→			sessionState = &strategy.SessionState{
   341→				SessionID: sessionID,
   342→			}
   343→		}
   344→		sessionState.CondensedTranscriptLines = totalLines
   345→		sessionState.CheckpointCount++
   346→		if updateErr := strategy.SaveSessionState(sessionState); updateErr != nil {
   347→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to update session state: %v\n", updateErr)
   348→		} else {
   349→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Updated session state: transcript position=%d, checkpoint=%d\n",
   350→				totalLines, sessionState.CheckpointCount)
   351→		}
   352→	}
   353→
   354→	// Clean up pre-prompt state (CLI responsibility)
   355→	if err := CleanupPrePromptState(sessionID); err != nil {
   356→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to cleanup pre-prompt state: %v\n", err)
   357→	}
   358→
   359→	return nil
   360→}

   362→// handleClaudeCodePostTodo handles the PostToolUse[TodoWrite] hook for subagent checkpoints.
   363→// Creates a checkpoint if we're in a subagent context (active pre-task file exists).
   364→// Skips silently if not in subagent context (main agent).
   365→func handleClaudeCodePostTodo() error {
   366→	input, err := parseSubagentCheckpointHookInput(os.Stdin)
   367→	if err != nil {
   368→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to parse PostToolUse[TodoWrite] input: %w", err)
   369→	}
   370→
   371→	// Get agent for logging context
   372→	ag, err := GetCurrentHookAgent()
   373→	if err != nil {
   374→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get agent: %w", err)
   375→	}
   376→
   377→	logCtx := logging.WithAgent(logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), "hooks"), ag.Name())
   378→	logging.Info(logCtx, "post-todo",
   379→		slog.String("hook", "post-todo"),
   380→		slog.String("hook_type", "subagent"),
   381→		slog.String("model_session_id", input.SessionID),
   382→		slog.String("transcript_path", input.TranscriptPath),
   383→		slog.String("tool_use_id", input.ToolUseID),
   384→	)
   385→
   386→	// Check if we're in a subagent context by looking for an active pre-task file
   387→	taskToolUseID, found := FindActivePreTaskFile()
   388→	if !found {
   389→		// Not in subagent context - this is a main agent TodoWrite, skip
   390→		return nil
   391→	}
   392→
   393→	// Skip on default branch to avoid polluting main/master history
   394→	if skip, branchName := ShouldSkipOnDefaultBranch(); skip {
   395→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Entire: skipping incremental checkpoint on branch '%s'\n", branchName)
   396→		return nil
   397→	}
   398→
   399→	// Detect file changes since last checkpoint
   400→	modified, newFiles, deleted, err := DetectChangedFiles()
   401→	if err != nil {
   402→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to detect changed files: %v\n", err)
   403→		return nil
   404→	}
   405→
   406→	// If no file changes, skip creating a checkpoint
   407→	if len(modified) == 0 && len(newFiles) == 0 && len(deleted) == 0 {
   408→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "[entire] No file changes detected, skipping incremental checkpoint\n")
   409→		return nil
   410→	}
   411→
   412→	// Get git author
   413→	author, err := GetGitAuthor()
   414→	if err != nil {
   415→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to get git author: %v\n", err)
   416→		return nil
   417→	}
   418→
   419→	// Get the active strategy
   420→	strat := GetStrategy()
   421→
   422→	// Ensure strategy setup is complete
   423→	if err := strat.EnsureSetup(); err != nil {
   424→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to ensure strategy setup: %v\n", err)
   425→		return nil
   426→	}
   427→
   428→	// Get the session ID from the transcript path or input, then transform to Entire session ID
   429→	sessionID := input.SessionID
   430→	if sessionID == "" {
   431→		sessionID = paths.ExtractSessionIDFromTranscriptPath(input.TranscriptPath)
   432→	}
   433→
   434→	// Get next checkpoint sequence
   435→	seq := GetNextCheckpointSequence(sessionID, taskToolUseID)
   436→
   437→	// Extract the todo content from the tool_input.
   438→	// PostToolUse receives the NEW todo list where the just-completed work is
   439→	// marked as "completed". The last completed item is the work that was just done.
   440→	todoContent := ExtractLastCompletedTodoFromToolInput(input.ToolInput)
   441→	if todoContent == "" {
   442→		// No completed items - this is likely the first TodoWrite (planning phase).
   443→		// Check if there are any todos at all to avoid duplicate messages.
   444→		todoCount := CountTodosFromToolInput(input.ToolInput)
   445→		if todoCount > 0 {
   446→			// Use "Planning: N todos" format for the first TodoWrite
   447→			todoContent = fmt.Sprintf("Planning: %d todos", todoCount)
   448→		}
   449→		// If todoCount == 0, todoContent remains empty and FormatIncrementalMessage
   450→		// will fall back to "Checkpoint #N" format
   451→	}
   452→
   453→	// Get agent type from the currently executing hook agent (authoritative source)
   454→	var agentType agent.AgentType
   455→	if hookAgent, agentErr := GetCurrentHookAgent(); agentErr == nil {
   456→		agentType = hookAgent.Type()
   457→	}
   458→
   459→	// Build incremental checkpoint context
   460→	ctx := strategy.TaskCheckpointContext{
   461→		SessionID:           sessionID,
   462→		ToolUseID:           taskToolUseID,
   463→		ModifiedFiles:       modified,
   464→		NewFiles:            newFiles,
   465→		DeletedFiles:        deleted,
   466→		TranscriptPath:      input.TranscriptPath,
   467→		AuthorName:          author.Name,
   468→		AuthorEmail:         author.Email,
   469→		IsIncremental:       true,
   470→		IncrementalSequence: seq,
   471→		IncrementalType:     input.ToolName,
   472→		IncrementalData:     input.ToolInput,
   473→		TodoContent:         todoContent,
   474→		AgentType:           agentType,
   475→	}
   476→
   477→	// Save incremental checkpoint
   478→	if err := strat.SaveTaskCheckpoint(ctx); err != nil {
   479→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to save incremental checkpoint: %v\n", err)
   480→		return nil
   481→	}
   482→
   483→	fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "[entire] Created incremental checkpoint #%d for %s (task: %s)\n",
   484→		seq, input.ToolName, taskToolUseID[:min(12, len(taskToolUseID))])
   485→	return nil
   486→}

   488→// handleClaudeCodePreTask handles the PreToolUse[Task] hook
   489→func handleClaudeCodePreTask() error {
   490→	// Skip on default branch for strategies that don't allow it
   491→	if skip, branchName := ShouldSkipOnDefaultBranchForStrategy(); skip {
   492→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Entire: skipping on branch '%s' - create a feature branch to use Entire tracking\n", branchName)
   493→		return nil // Don't fail the hook, just skip
   494→	}
   495→
   496→	input, err := parseTaskHookInput(os.Stdin)
   497→	if err != nil {
   498→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to parse PreToolUse[Task] input: %w", err)
   499→	}
   500→
   501→	// Get agent for logging context
   502→	ag, err := GetCurrentHookAgent()
   503→	if err != nil {
   504→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get agent: %w", err)
   505→	}
   506→
   507→	logCtx := logging.WithAgent(logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), "hooks"), ag.Name())
   508→	logging.Info(logCtx, "pre-task",
   509→		slog.String("hook", "pre-task"),
   510→		slog.String("hook_type", "subagent"),
   511→		slog.String("model_session_id", input.SessionID),
   512→		slog.String("transcript_path", input.TranscriptPath),
   513→		slog.String("tool_use_id", input.ToolUseID),
   514→	)
   515→
   516→	// Log context to stdout
   517→	logPreTaskHookContext(os.Stdout, input)
   518→
   519→	// Capture pre-task state locally (for computing new files when task completes).
   520→	// We don't create a shadow branch commit here. Commits are created during
   521→	// task completion (handleClaudeCodePostTask/handleClaudeCodePostTodo) only if the task resulted
   522→	// in file changes.
   523→	if err := CapturePreTaskState(input.ToolUseID); err != nil {
   524→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to capture pre-task state: %w", err)
   525→	}
   526→
   527→	return nil
   528→}

   530→// handleClaudeCodePostTask handles the PostToolUse[Task] hook
   531→func handleClaudeCodePostTask() error {
   532→	// Skip on default branch for strategies that don't allow it
   533→	if skip, branchName := ShouldSkipOnDefaultBranchForStrategy(); skip {
   534→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Entire: skipping on branch '%s' - create a feature branch to use Entire tracking\n", branchName)
   535→		return nil // Don't fail the hook, just skip
   536→	}
   537→
   538→	input, err := parsePostTaskHookInput(os.Stdin)
   539→	if err != nil {
   540→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to parse PostToolUse[Task] input: %w", err)
   541→	}
   542→
   543→	// Extract subagent type from tool_input for logging
   544→	subagentType, taskDescription := ParseSubagentTypeAndDescription(input.ToolInput)
   545→
   546→	// Get agent for logging context
   547→	ag, err := GetCurrentHookAgent()
   548→	if err != nil {
   549→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get agent: %w", err)
   550→	}
   551→
   552→	// Log parsed input context
   553→	logCtx := logging.WithAgent(logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), "hooks"), ag.Name())
   554→	logging.Info(logCtx, "post-task",
   555→		slog.String("hook", "post-task"),
   556→		slog.String("hook_type", "subagent"),
   557→		slog.String("tool_use_id", input.ToolUseID),
   558→		slog.String("agent_id", input.AgentID),
   559→		slog.String("subagent_type", subagentType),
   560→	)
   561→
   562→	// Determine subagent transcript path
   563→	transcriptDir := filepath.Dir(input.TranscriptPath)
   564→	var subagentTranscriptPath string
   565→	if input.AgentID != "" {
   566→		subagentTranscriptPath = AgentTranscriptPath(transcriptDir, input.AgentID)
   567→		if !fileExists(subagentTranscriptPath) {
   568→			subagentTranscriptPath = ""
   569→		}
   570→	}
   571→
   572→	// Log context to stdout
   573→	logPostTaskHookContext(os.Stdout, input, subagentTranscriptPath)
   574→
   575→	// Parse transcript to extract modified files
   576→	var modifiedFiles []string
   577→	if subagentTranscriptPath != "" {
   578→		// Use subagent transcript if available
   579→		transcript, err := parseTranscript(subagentTranscriptPath)
   580→		if err != nil {
   581→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to parse subagent transcript: %v\n", err)
   582→		} else {
   583→			modifiedFiles = extractModifiedFiles(transcript)
   584→		}
   585→	} else {
   586→		// Fall back to main transcript
   587→		transcript, err := parseTranscript(input.TranscriptPath)
   588→		if err != nil {
   589→			fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to parse transcript: %v\n", err)
   590→		} else {
   591→			modifiedFiles = extractModifiedFiles(transcript)
   592→		}
   593→	}
   594→
   595→	// Load pre-task state and compute new files
   596→	preState, err := LoadPreTaskState(input.ToolUseID)
   597→	if err != nil {
   598→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to load pre-task state: %v\n", err)
   599→	}
   600→	newFiles, err := ComputeNewFilesFromTask(preState)
   601→	if err != nil {
   602→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to compute new files: %v\n", err)
   603→	}
   604→
   605→	// Get repo root for path conversion (not cwd, since Claude may be in a subdirectory)
   606→	// Using cwd would filter out files in sibling directories (paths starting with ..)
   607→	repoRoot, err := paths.RepoRoot()
   608→	if err != nil {
   609→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get repo root: %w", err)
   610→	}
   611→
   612→	// Filter and normalize paths
   613→	relModifiedFiles := FilterAndNormalizePaths(modifiedFiles, repoRoot)
   614→	relNewFiles := FilterAndNormalizePaths(newFiles, repoRoot)
   615→
   616→	// If no file changes, skip creating a checkpoint
   617→	if len(relModifiedFiles) == 0 && len(relNewFiles) == 0 {
   618→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "[entire] No file changes detected, skipping task checkpoint\n")
   619→		// Cleanup pre-task state (ignore error - cleanup is best-effort)
   620→		_ = CleanupPreTaskState(input.ToolUseID) //nolint:errcheck // best-effort cleanup
   621→		return nil
   622→	}
   623→
   624→	// Find checkpoint UUID from main transcript (best-effort, ignore errors)

   679→// handleClaudeCodeSessionStart handles the SessionStart hook for Claude Code.
   680→func handleClaudeCodeSessionStart() error {
   681→	return handleSessionStartCommon()
   682→}
   683→
   684→// handleClaudeCodeSessionEnd handles the SessionEnd hook for Claude Code.
   685→// This fires when the user explicitly closes the session.
   686→// Updates the session state with EndedAt timestamp.
   687→func handleClaudeCodeSessionEnd() error {
   688→	ag, err := GetCurrentHookAgent()
   689→	if err != nil {
   690→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to get agent: %w", err)
   691→	}
   692→
   693→	input, err := ag.ParseHookInput(agent.HookSessionEnd, os.Stdin)
   694→	if err != nil {
   695→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to parse hook input: %w", err)
   696→	}
   697→
   698→	logCtx := logging.WithAgent(logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), "hooks"), ag.Name())
   699→	logging.Info(logCtx, "session-end",
   700→		slog.String("hook", "session-end"),
   701→		slog.String("hook_type", "agent"),
   702→		slog.String("model_session_id", input.SessionID),
   703→	)
   704→
   705→	if input.SessionID == "" {
   706→		return nil // No session to update
   707→	}
   708→
   709→	// Best-effort cleanup - don't block session closure on failure
   710→	if err := markSessionEnded(input.SessionID); err != nil {
   711→		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Warning: failed to mark session ended: %v\n", err)
   712→	}
   713→	return nil
   714→}
   715→
   716→// markSessionEnded updates the session state with the current time as EndedAt.
   717→func markSessionEnded(sessionID string) error {
   718→	state, err := strategy.LoadSessionState(sessionID)
   719→	if err != nil {
   720→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to load session state: %w", err)
   721→	}
   722→	if state == nil {
   723→		return nil // No state file, nothing to update
   724→	}
   725→
   726→	now := time.Now()
   727→	state.EndedAt = &now
   728→
   729→	if err := strategy.SaveSessionState(state); err != nil {
   730→		return fmt.Errorf("failed to save session state: %w", err)
   731→	}
   732→	return nil
   733→}

   509→// buildCommitMessage constructs the commit message with proper trailers.

   512→func (s *GitStore) buildCommitMessage(opts WriteCommittedOptions, taskMetadataPath string) string {
   513→	var commitMsg strings.Builder
   514→
   515→	// Subject line is always the checkpoint ID for consistent formatting
   516→	commitMsg.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("Checkpoint: %s\n\n", opts.CheckpointID))

   519→	if opts.CommitSubject != "" {

   522→	commitMsg.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", trailers.SessionTrailerKey, opts.SessionID))
   523→	commitMsg.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s\n", trailers.StrategyTrailerKey, opts.Strategy))
   524→	if opts.Agent != "" {

    26→// listCheckpoints returns all checkpoints from the sessions branch.
    27→// Uses checkpoint.GitStore.ListCommitted() for reading from entire/sessions.
    28→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) listCheckpoints() ([]CheckpointInfo, error) {
    29→	store, err := s.getCheckpointStore()
    30→	if err != nil {
    31→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to get checkpoint store: %w", err)
    32→	}
    33→
    34→	committed, err := store.ListCommitted(context.Background())
    35→	if err != nil {
    36→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to list committed checkpoints: %w", err)
    37→	}
    38→
    39→	// Convert from checkpoint.CommittedInfo to strategy.CheckpointInfo
    40→	result := make([]CheckpointInfo, 0, len(committed))
    41→	for _, c := range committed {
    42→		result = append(result, CheckpointInfo{
    43→			CheckpointID:     c.CheckpointID,
    44→			SessionID:        c.SessionID,
    45→			CreatedAt:        c.CreatedAt,
    46→			CheckpointsCount: c.CheckpointsCount,
    47→			FilesTouched:     c.FilesTouched,
    48→			Agent:            c.Agent,
    49→			IsTask:           c.IsTask,
    50→			ToolUseID:        c.ToolUseID,
    51→			SessionCount:     c.SessionCount,
    52→			SessionIDs:       c.SessionIDs,
    53→		})
    54→	}
    55→
    56→	return result, nil
    57→}
    58→
    59→// getCheckpointsForSession returns all checkpoints for a session ID.
    60→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) getCheckpointsForSession(sessionID string) ([]CheckpointInfo, error) {
    61→	all, err := s.listCheckpoints()
    62→	if err != nil {
    63→		return nil, err
    64→	}
    65→
    66→	var result []CheckpointInfo
    67→	for _, cp := range all {
    68→		if cp.SessionID == sessionID || strings.HasPrefix(cp.SessionID, sessionID) {
    69→			result = append(result, cp)
    70→		}
    71→	}
    72→
    73→	if len(result) == 0 {
    74→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("no checkpoints for session: %s", sessionID)
    75→	}
    76→
    77→	return result, nil
    78→}
    79→
    80→// getCheckpointLog returns the transcript for a specific checkpoint ID.
    81→// Uses checkpoint.GitStore.ReadCommitted() for reading from entire/sessions.
    82→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) getCheckpointLog(checkpointID id.CheckpointID) ([]byte, error) {
    83→	store, err := s.getCheckpointStore()
    84→	if err != nil {
    85→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to get checkpoint store: %w", err)
    86→	}
    87→
    88→	content, err := store.ReadLatestSessionContent(context.Background(), checkpointID)
    89→	if err != nil {
    90→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to read checkpoint: %w", err)
    91→	}
    92→	if content == nil {
    93→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("checkpoint not found: %s", checkpointID)
    94→	}
    95→	if len(content.Transcript) == 0 {
    96→		return nil, fmt.Errorf("no transcript found for checkpoint: %s", checkpointID)
    97→	}
    98→
    99→	return content.Transcript, nil
   100→}

   191→func calculateSessionAttributions(repo *git.Repository, shadowRef *plumbing.Reference, sessionData *ExtractedSessionData, state *SessionState) *cpkg.InitialAttribution {
   192→	// Calculate initial attribution using accumulated prompt attribution data.
   193→	// This uses user edits captured at each prompt start (before agent works),
   194→	// plus any user edits after the final checkpoint (shadow → head).
   195→	logCtx := logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), "attribution")
   196→	var attribution *cpkg.InitialAttribution
   197→	headRef, headErr := repo.Head()
   198→	if headErr != nil {
   199→		logging.Debug(logCtx, "attribution skipped: failed to get HEAD",
   200→			slog.String("error", headErr.Error()))
   201→	} else {
   202→		headCommit, commitErr := repo.CommitObject(headRef.Hash())
   203→		if commitErr != nil {
   204→			logging.Debug(logCtx, "attribution skipped: failed to get HEAD commit",
   205→				slog.String("error", commitErr.Error()))
   206→		} else {
   207→			headTree, treeErr := headCommit.Tree()
   208→			if treeErr != nil {
   209→				logging.Debug(logCtx, "attribution skipped: failed to get HEAD tree",
   210→					slog.String("error", treeErr.Error()))
   211→			} else {
   212→				// Get shadow branch tree (checkpoint tree - what the agent wrote)
   213→				shadowCommit, shadowErr := repo.CommitObject(shadowRef.Hash())
   214→				if shadowErr != nil {
   215→					logging.Debug(logCtx, "attribution skipped: failed to get shadow commit",
   216→						slog.String("error", shadowErr.Error()),
   217→						slog.String("shadow_ref", shadowRef.Hash().String()))
   218→				} else {
   219→					shadowTree, shadowTreeErr := shadowCommit.Tree()
   220→					if shadowTreeErr != nil {
   221→						logging.Debug(logCtx, "attribution skipped: failed to get shadow tree",
   222→							slog.String("error", shadowTreeErr.Error()))
   223→					} else {
